cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.HC 

This paper is about developing a neural user simulator for training task-oriented dialogue systems. It involves natural language processing, machine learning, and human-computer interaction. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves evaluating the performance of the simulator and the trained policies on real users, which falls under the sub-categories cs.SD (Sound) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
